			<hr />
		
			<div class="post">
				<h3>Re: BitTorrent Sync on stora???</h3>
				<div class="date"><img src="./styles/absolution/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" />Posted: <strong>Sun Aug 11, 2013 10:35 pm</strong></div>
				<div class="author">by <strong>jberghuis</strong></div>
				<div class="content">BitTorrent Sync is a great personal self-hosted cloud alternative to Dropbox. <br /><br />I have managed to get BitTorrent Sync running on the Stora with no issues so far.  <br />Below is how I did it (based on instructions for the Raspberry Pi, <a href="http://jack.minardi.org/raspberry_pi/replace-dropbox-with-bittorrent-sync-and-a-raspberry-pi/" class="postlink">http://jack.minardi.org/raspberry_pi/replace-dropbox-with-bittorrent-sync-and-a-raspberry-pi/</a>)<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000">I'm not a professional coder, so please let me if I'm doing something terribly wrong! Also let me know how it can be improved.</span></span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Installing BitTorrent Sync on the Netgear Stora</span><br /><br />You need to make a directory, grab the ARM build of BitTorrent Sync and uncompress it:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>mkdir ~/.btsync &amp;&amp; cd ~/.btsync<br />wget http://btsync.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/btsync_arm.tar.gz<br />tar xvfz btsync_arm.tar.gz</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Now you only have to launch the btsync application:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>cd ~/.btsync<br />sudo ./btsync</code></dd></dl><br /><br />If you see the following output btsync is properly running (your pid will be different).<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>BitTorrent Sync forked to background. pid = 3003</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Navigate your browser to <span style="font-weight: bold">Your-Stora-IP-Address:8888</span> to manage your syncing. To add a folder click &quot;Add Folder&quot; and navigate to it. You will need to generate a secret as this is the first time you are adding the folder. You use the same secret for the folder you want to sync on your other device.<br /><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Starting at Boot</span><br /><br />You may want to set btsync to start when you boot your Stora. To do that we will place a script in /etc/init.d/ and then register it with chkconfig. First open in nano:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>sudo nano /etc/init.d/btsync</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Paste the following code in the script. Replace <span style="font-weight: bold">&lt;&lt;username&gt;&gt;</span> with your Stora username.<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>!/bin/sh<br /># chkconfig: 2345 95 20<br /># description: btsync<br /># processname: Starting btsync.<br /># /etc/init.d/btsync<br />#<br /># Carry out specific functions when asked to by the system<br />case &quot;$1&quot; in<br />start)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; /home/&lt;&lt;username&gt;&gt;/.btsync/btsync<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ;;<br />stop)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; killall btsync<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ;;<br />*)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; echo &quot;Usage: /etc/init.d/btsync {start|stop}&quot;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; exit 1<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; ;;<br />esac<br />exit 0<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br />Save and exit.<br />Then change the permissions, test, and register it to run at boot:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>sudo chmod 755 /etc/init.d/btsync<br />sudo /etc/init.d/btsync start<br />sudo /etc/init.d/btsync stop<br />sudo /sbin/chkconfig --add btsync<br />sudo /sbin/chkconfig --levels 2345 btsync on<br /></code></dd></dl><br /><br />Restart your Stora to check whether BTSync will autostart on boot:<br /><br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Select all</a></dt><dd><code>shutdown -r now</code></dd></dl><br /><br />Navigate your browser to <span style="font-weight: bold">Your-Stora-IP-Address:8888</span> to see if it works.</div>
			</div>
